primaryTopic.definition: The School of Earth and Environmental Sciences delivers practical solutions to the complex issues that affect our physical environment and how we interact with it. The school was formed in 2017 and consolidated two former schools - the School of Earth Sciences, and the School of Geography, Planning and Environmental Management.
